.TH AutoBDP 1 "July 2026" "v1.0.0" "AutoBDP Manual"
.SH NAME
AutoBDP \- Automated Binary Decompiler Pipeline
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B AutoBDP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B AutoBDP
is an automated reverse engineering framework designed to bridge the gap between static binary decompilation and compilable C source code. 

The framework handles raw binary ingestion, automates headless analysis via Ghidra, extracts static global memory spaces (.rodata/.data), maps low-level assembly targets, and passes the context to a Large Language Model (LLM) to synthesize structured C program files.

To guarantee functional correctness, it incorporates a closed-loop, self-healing compiler verification stack using GCC and executes fuzzy structural similarity diffing via system call tracing (strace).
.SH FEATURES
.TP
.B Headless Automation
Invokes headless Ghidra routines to dump clean pseudo-C blocks and synchronized assembly layouts automatically.
.TP
.B Memory Space Extraction
Maps physical segment targets directly into a generated header file to maintain exact binary pointer parity.
.TP
.B Self-Healing Compilation
Traps GCC compilation faults programmatically, passing error diagnostics back to the synthesis model for inline fixes.
.TP
.B Behavioral Verification
Validates program execution logic against the original binary by checking normalized system call execution streams.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/Desktop/<program_name>_folder/
The target workspace directory automatically generated by the script to store data Extractions, assembly text, system traces, and the final compiled binary.
